# ============================================================================
# Flight Rescheduler - Environment Variables Template
# ============================================================================
#
# IMPORTANT: This project uses Convex for the backend.
# Most environment variables should be set in the Convex Dashboard, NOT in a .env file.
#
# Setup Instructions:
# 1. Go to https://dashboard.convex.dev
# 2. Select your project → Settings → Environment Variables
# 3. Add the variables marked "CONVEX DASHBOARD" below
#
# ============================================================================

# ===== CONVEX DEPLOYMENT URL =====
# This is automatically generated when you run: npx convex dev
# You don't need to set this manually - Convex handles it
# CONVEX_DEPLOYMENT=

# ===== ADD TO CONVEX DASHBOARD =====
# Go to: https://dashboard.convex.dev → Your Project → Settings → Environment Variables

# Weather API Key (REQUIRED)
# Get your free key from: https://openweathermap.org/api
# Free tier: 1,000 calls/day
# CONVEX DASHBOARD: OPENWEATHER_API_KEY=your_openweather_api_key_here

# AI Provider Key (REQUIRED - Choose ONE)
# Option 1: OpenAI (Recommended - GPT-4o-mini)
# Get key from: https://platform.openai.com/api-keys
# CONVEX DASHBOARD: OPENAI_API_KEY=your_openai_api_key_here

# Option 2: Anthropic (Claude 3.5 Sonnet)
# Get key from: https://console.anthropic.com/
# CONVEX DASHBOARD: ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=your_anthropic_api_key_here

# ============================================================================
# QUICK START
# ============================================================================
# 
# 1. Install dependencies:
#    npm install
#
# 2. Start Convex (generates deployment):
#    npx convex dev
#
# 3. Add API keys to Convex Dashboard:
#    - Go to https://dashboard.convex.dev
#    - Add OPENWEATHER_API_KEY
#    - Add OPENAI_API_KEY (or ANTHROPIC_API_KEY)
#
# 4. Start frontend:
#    npm run dev:frontend
#
# 5. Open dashboard:
#    http://localhost:5173
#
# ============================================================================
# SECURITY NOTES
# ============================================================================
#
# - Convex environment variables are secure and never exposed to the frontend
# - Never commit .env files with real API keys to git
# - The .gitignore file protects against accidental commits
# - Use separate keys for development and production
#
